Motorola has launched two new smartphones, the Moto E4 and E4 Plus. The company said the devices deliver “the things you want”, including all-day battery life, a good display, and an advanced camera. The devices are aimed at the more affordable end of the smartphone market, and will sell for: Motorola said the standout feature of the Plus model is its 5.5″ HD display and large battery, which comes in at 5,000mAh. The device also features a 10W rapid charger, which gives you “hours of battery life in minutes of charging”. The smartphones will be available in a variety of metal finishes beginning this month.  